 Jewish (Ashkenazic); Swedish (also <b>Lång</b>): nickname for a tall person, from Older Scots, Middle English, Middle High German, Middle Dutch, and Danish <i>lang</i> ‘long’, Swedish <i>lång</i>. The surname of (Middle High) German origin is also found in France (mainly Alsace and Lorraine), Czechia, Hungary, Poland, Slovakia, Croatia, and Slovenia.","Hungarian (<b>Láng</b>): from <i>láng</i> ‘flame’, hence probably a nickname for a passionate person, or a man with a fighting spirit. Alternatively, it may be an indirect occupational name for a smith or someone who worked with fire. This surname is also found in Slovenia, where it is spelled <i>Lang</i>, and in Slovakia, where it is spelled in both ways.","Chinese: Mandarin form of the surname 郎, an ancient term to refer to one's lover or son: (i) from the placename Lang (郎), the name of a city, the living place of Fei Bo, the grandson of the Duke Yi of Lu (ruler of the state of Lu, reigned 815–807  BC ). Some of his descendants later changed their original surname Fei to Lang (郎). (ii) borne by some families from the state of the South Huns (48–216  AD , located in northern China)."]},{"name":"Longe","meanings":["Altered form of French   Lange   2.","French: from the feminine form of   Long   ‘long, tall’.","French (<b>Longé</b>): derivative of Old French <i>longe</i> ‘(leather) thong’, used in a transferred sense as a topographic name for someone who lived on a long, narrow stretch of terrain."]},{"name":"Langa","meanings":["Spanish: habitational name from any of the places called Langa in Ávila, Soria, and in particular Zaragoza provinces.","Polish adaptation and, in some cases, also an Americanized form of German   Lange  ."]}]},{"name":"Jan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Jan De Lange was born about 1375, in Antwerp, Belgium. He had at least 1 daughter with Katharina Sanders."},"et":{"circa 1375–":"umbes 1375–Surnud","1380–Female":"1380–Surnud","1400–1432":"1400–1432","1375–Male":"1375–Surnud","circa 1375":"umbes 1375","1400":"1400","1432":"1432","1375":"1375","1380":"1380","Antwerpen, België":"Antwerpen, Belgia"},"fi":{"circa 1375–":"noin 1375–Kuollut","1380–Female":"1380–Kuollut","1400–1432":"1400–1432","1375–Male":"1375–Kuollut","circa 1375":"noin 1375","1400":"1400","1432":"1432","1375":"1375","1380":"1380","Antwerpen, België":"Antwerpen, Belgia"},"fr":{"circa 1375–":"environ 1375–Décédé","1380–Female":"1380–Décédée","1400–1432":"1400–1432","1375–Male":"1375–Décédé","circa 1375":"environ 1375","1400":"1400","1432":"1432","1375":"1375","1380":"1380","Antwerpen, België":"Anvers, Belgique","lifeSummary":"Jan De Lange est né environ 1375, à Anvers, Belgique. Il a eu au moins 1 fille avec Katharina Sanders."},"de":{"circa 1375–":"um 1375–Verstorben","1380–Female":"1380–Verstorben","1400–1432":"1400–1432","1375–Male":"1375–Verstorben","circa 1375":"um 1375","1400":"1400","1432":"1432","1375":"1375","1380":"1380","Antwerpen, België":"Antwerpen, Belgien","lifeSummary":"Jan De Lange wurde um 1375 in Antwerpen, Belgien geboren. Er hatte mit Katharina Sanders mindestens 1 Tochter."},"ht":{"circa 1375–":"about 1375–Desede","1380–Female":"1380–Desede","1400–1432":"1400–1432","1375–Male":"1375–Desede","circa 1375":"about 1375","1400":"1400","1432":"1432","1375":"1375","1380":"1380","Antwerpen, België":"Antwerpen, Belgique"},"hu":{"circa 1375–":"1375 körül–elhunyt","1380–Female":"1380–elhunyt","1400–1432":"1400–1432","1375–Male":"1375–elhunyt","circa 1375":"1375 körül","1400":"1400","1432":"1432","1375":"1375","1380":"1380","